ach response stays under 3 seconds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.77,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"An event whose ID was already received is not written to the queue a second time.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: dedupe correctness is at boundary between handler, idempotency store/constraint, and queue write path. Unit tests of an in-memory set can miss persistence/transactional wiring issues. REAL-INFRA: local DB/filesystem-backed dedupe and queue in one process is sufficient; no real network/subprocess required. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: not applicable. Rejection-gate: System was considered but rejected because no behavior text requires external network or OS-specific primitives beyond local module+storage integration.","test_description":"Using a real local persistence layer for idempotency, submit the same event ID twice and assert first request enqueues once while second request does not create a second queue record.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the queue reports it is full, the handler returns 503 with a Retry-After header.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is mapping a queue-layer condition to HTTP semantics (status + header), a module handoff concern. Unit-only tests can miss middleware/response composition issues. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network/subprocess required; in-process app with queue-full signal is enough. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: not applicable. Rejection-gate: System was considered but rejected because behavior does not require real network failures or OS behavior, only correct error translation.","test_description":"Wire handler with a queue adapter that returns a concrete 'full' error/state, issue request in-process, asse